Durban - Two people were killed and two other injured after a truck and car collided on the N3 on Thursday. The crash occurred at the Applesden turn in Pietermaritzburg. Russel Meiring, spokesperson for ER24, said emergency teams arrived at the scene to find both vehicles had veered down the embankment at the side of the road.  “The light motor vehicle was found partially beneath the bed of the truck. Several trees had collapsed and fallen onto the truck,” Meiring said.  Two men, one from each vehicle, succumbed to their injuries and were declared dead at the scene.  Meiring said other patients were stabilised at the scene and found to have sustained only minor to moderate injuries.  Paramedics treated the patients and thereafter transported them to nearby provincial hospitals for further care,” he said.  Police are investigating the cause of the crash. Daily News